org.hibernate.cache.internal

Class CollectionCacheInvalidator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.hibernate.cache.internal.CollectionCacheInvalidator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable, PostDeleteEventListener, PostInsertEventListener, PostUpdateEventListener, Integrator

    public class CollectionCacheInvalidator
extends java.lang.Object
implements Integrator, PostInsertEventListener, PostDeleteEventListener, PostUpdateEventListener
    Allows the collection cache to be automatically evicted if an element is inserted/removed/updated *without* properly managing both sides of the association (ie, the ManyToOne collection is changed w/o properly managing the OneToMany). For this functionality to be used, AvailableSettings.AUTO_EVICT_COLLECTION_CACHE must be enabled. For performance reasons, it's disabled by default.
